    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="43"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/10092 ½a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to">Colonel E. M. House</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-07">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">May</hi> 7, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to"
                            >Colonel</persName>
                    </hi>: I saw the President today in regard to the expansion and continuation of
                    the Commission of Inquiry, of which Doctor <persName corresp="#p_MSE1"
                        >Mezes</persName> is the head. He approved thoroughly going on with the work
                    and will furnish the necessary funds. Will you be good enough to advise Doctor
                        <persName corresp="#p_MSE1">Mezes</persName> of this and to have him let me
                    know what additional funds are required and when?</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>[File copy not signed]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
